# Owned Plugin Development Rules

This repo is a fork of Apache DevLake. Our team owns only three plugins:
`aireview`, `codecov`, `testregistry`. Do NOT modify upstream code outside these directories.

## Plugin Checklist (every change)

- [ ] All models listed in `GetTablesInfo()` in `impl/impl.go`
- [ ] New models have a migration script in `models/migrationscripts/` AND registered in `register.go:All()`
- [ ] Migration filename: `YYYYMMDD_description.go`
- [ ] Apache 2.0 license header on every new `.go` file
- [ ] No cross-plugin imports (`plugins/X` must not import `plugins/Y`)
- [ ] Secrets use `serializer:encdec` gorm tag, sanitized in API responses

## Testing

```bash
cd backend
go test ./plugins/<plugin>/... -v        # unit tests
go vet ./plugins/<plugin>/...            # vet
golangci-lint run ./plugins/<plugin>/... # lint
```

E2E tests (aireview only, needs MySQL with `lake_test`):
```bash
export E2E_DB_URL="mysql://merico:merico@localhost:3306/lake_test?charset=utf8mb4&parseTime=True"
go test ./plugins/aireview/e2e/... -v
```

## Common Patterns

- **Data-source plugin** (codecov, testregistry): Connection → Scope → ScopeConfig → Collector → Extractor → Converter
- **Metric plugin** (aireview): No connection; uses domain-layer data from github/gitlab; configured via Projects
- **Subtask ordering**: Defined by `SubTaskMetas()` in `impl/impl.go` — order matters
- **New migration**: Create file, add struct with `Up()`, register in `All()`
